Introducing: μgit?
μgit (ugit) is a small implementation of a Git-like version control system (VCS).
doesn't compress objects.
doesn't save the mode of the files.
doesn't save the time of a commit.


Why not learn Git by reading the real Git code?
'Git SourceCode' deals with a lot of edge cases that we don't care about for learning.
In this tutorial we will focus on the bare minimum to get the point across.




